# Agent: Memory Bank Levels

## L1 — Quick fix

Examples: typo, one-line fix, obvious condition, small docs correction.

Process: short plan → edit → minimal validation → report.

## L2 — Local enhancement

Examples: one button, one form behavior, one report setting, one local EPF improvement.

Process: VAN → PLAN → BUILD → REFLECT/ARCHIVE light.

## L3 — Feature

Examples: extension feature, new EPF/ERF, several modules, report with SKD, exchange scenario, register changes.

Process: VAN → PLAN → CREATIVE if needed → BUILD → REFLECT → ARCHIVE.

## L4 — System/architecture

Examples: migration, integration, several subsystems, architecture of local LLM ↔ Cursor ↔ MCP tools, mass data correction with accounting impact.

Process: full Memory Bank, design document, phased implementation, rollback plan, expanded verification.

## Escalate if touches

- posting/register movements;
- RLS/roles;
- transactions/locks;
- public export API;
- adopted objects in extension;
- background/scheduled jobs;
- integrations;
- mass data correction.

